# Insurance Claim Fraud Detection — Executive Summary

An unsupervised anomaly-detection pipeline (deep autoencoder + Isolation Forest, cross-validated against each other, plus three hard-coded collusion rules) was run against **10,000 claims** worth **$165,638,300** in total exposure.

## Headline numbers

- **738 claims (7.4% of volume)** were flagged for review.
- Those claims represent **$11,244,300** in exposure — **6.8%** of total portfolio dollar value.

## Priority tiers

| Tier | Claims | Dollar Value | Trigger |
|---|---|---|---|
| CRITICAL | 12 | $275,000 | Hard collusion rule fired (shared bank account, address, or last name between agent & customer) |
| HIGH | 259 | $4,292,400 | Both models (autoencoder + isolation forest) independently flagged this claim |
| MEDIUM | 467 | $6,676,900 | Exactly one model flagged this claim |
| LOW | 9,262 | $0 | Not flagged |

